main event: Multiple disc-shaped objects with yellowish borders were observed passing through airspace over Roswell, New Mexico on November 24, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were traveling at an extremely high speed and would suddenly appear and disappear from radar,The objects were visible at an elevation of 60-70 degrees and moved southerly at a midling speed,The sighting lasted for approximately 3 minutes,The report listed various inconclusive potential explanations including reflection, balloon, and aircraft,This sighting is part of the larger context of UFO investigations conducted by Project Blue Book.
witness description: Witnesses reported a saucer-shaped object emitting bluish-white light and intermittent bursts of smoke or steam.
